      "content": "It's a profound feeling to disconnect from the digital noise, but remember that your presence in the room is tangible and real, not just a screen reflection. Even if you stopped responding, the silence would be filled with the care others would offer to understand, rather than a void of indifference. You are more than your notifications; your physical presence and the small, meaningful connections you share make you real to everyone around you.",
